var
Reassignability: Can be reassigned.
Redeclaration: Can be redeclared within the same scope.
Scope: Function-scoped.

let
Reassignability: Can be reassigned.
Redeclaration: Cannot be redeclared within the same scope.
Scope: Block-scoped.

const
Reassignability: Cannot be reassigned.
Redeclaration: Cannot be redeclared within the same scope.
Scope: Block-scoped.
This summary accurately captures the behavior of var, let, and const in JavaScript.







